  "prompt": "Why am I unable to remove the Quora Community topic from a question?",
  "response": "You're likely unable to remove the \"Quora Community\" topic from a question for one of the following reasons:\n\n*   **It's a mandatory topic:** Quora often makes \"Quora Community\" a mandatory topic for questions that pertain to the platform itself. These are questions *about* Quora, its features, policies, users, etc. The idea is to ensure the question is seen by those who are most likely to have answers.\n\n*   **Quora's system prevents its removal:** Quora's algorithms might sometimes prevent you from removing a topic if it deems it highly relevant, even if you disagree. This is particularly true for automated topic suggestions.\n\n*   **Temporary technical issue:** There might be a temporary bug or glitch on Quora's platform that's preventing you from making changes.\n\nHere's what you can try:\n\n1.  **Double-check the question's content:** Review your question carefully. Is there any element that relates to Quora itself? Even if it seems tangential, the algorithm might be picking up on it. If the question is purely about something else entirely (e.g., \"What's the best way to learn French?\"), then \"Quora Community\" is likely inappropriate.\n\n2.  **Edit the question:** Try rephrasing your question to remove any possible ambiguity that might be triggering the \"Quora Community\" topic. Focus on the core subject matter.\n\n3.  **Contact Quora support:** If you're confident that the topic is irrelevant and you've tried editing, your best bet is to contact Quora support directly. Explain the situation clearly, stating why you believe the topic is inappropriate for your question. They may be able to manually remove it. To do this, scroll to the bottom of any Quora page and click \"Contact Us\".\n\nIn general, it's best to just leave the topic if you don't have a strong objection. Having an extra topic is less harmful than having a question that doesn't reach the right audience. However, if you believe it's truly misleading, contacting support is the best approach.\n",
